tasks.description: Task to get the Jenkins Crumb value.
tasks.helpContent:
Task to get Jenkins Crumb value for users


The crumb is a secret that is shared by the server and the client. If the Jenkins server receives a request that does not have the 'secret' then it ignores the request or returns an invalid crumb error. This prevents the use of the API on the server by unauthorized requestors.

Input Params:

  • Jenkins_IP: Provide the Jenkins host or IP with its protocol(https://10.10.100.89)
  • Username: Provide the username of the Jenkins user
  • API_Token: Provide the API Token of the Jenkins user

To generate an API Token: a) Login to Jenkins b) Click on User Configuration c) Click Add New Token

Task to trigger Jenkins Job based on the Job Name


Input Parameters:

  • Jenkins_IP: Provide the Jenkins host or IP with its protocol(https://10.10.100.89)
  • Job_Name: Provide the job name to trigger on Jenkins
  • Jenkins_Crumb: Provide the Jenkins crumb(use the Create Jenkins Crumb task to get the crumb value)
  • Parameters(In payload): Enter the parameters required to trigger the pipeline job

"parameter": [

{

"app name": "app services provisioning",

"Port": "443",

"Email": "emailaddress@gmail.com"

}

]

  • Username: Provide the username of the Jenkins user
  • API_Token: Provide the API Token of the Jenkins user

To generate an API Token: a) Login to Jenkins b) Click on User Configuration c) Click Add New Token
